event.message: %1 QoS policies successfully refreshed. No changes detected.
%1 QoS policies successfully refreshed. Policy changes detected.
The Advanced QoS Setting for inbound TCP throughput level successfully refreshed. %1
The Advanced QoS Setting for DSCP marking overrides successfully refreshed. %1
Selective application of legacy QoS policies based on domain or non-domain network category has been disabled on this machine. QoS policies will be applied to all network interfaces.
In the past %1 hour(s) and %2 minute(s), %3 HTTP.SYS responses have had their application requested QoS conflict with URL QoS policies.

There is at least one policy containing minimum bandwidth specification and at least one other policy that does not. It is generally not a good idea to mix these two classes of policies on the same system.
A %1 QoS policy "%2" has an invalid version number. This policy will not be applied.
A %1 QoS policy "%2" does not specify a QoS parameter (e.g. DSCP value, throttle rate, etc.) This policy will not be applied.
A %1 QoS policy "%2" potentially conflicts with other QoS policies. See documentation for rules about which policy will be applied at packet send time.

A %1 QoS policy "%2" was ignored because the application path could not be processed. The application path may be totally invalid, or has an invalid drive letter, or contains network-mapped drive letter.
%1 QoS policies failed to refresh. Error code: %2
A %1 QoS policy exceeds the maximum allowed name length. The offending policy is listed under the relevant policy root key with index %2.
A %1 QoS policy has a zero length name. The offending policy is listed under the relevant policy root key with index %2.
Failed to open the registry subkey for a %1 QoS policy. The policy is listed under the relevant policy root key with index %2.
Failed to read or validate the "%2" field for %1 QoS policy named "%3".
